      },
      "lineNbr": 29,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-21T22:13:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I was intentionally diverging as an experiment.  The intent was to make it so that only get() could create an instance.  However, this has a fatal flaw, anyone can create an instance using LazyInstance\u003cAutomationController\u003e.  Given that I want to encapsulate functionality more, I\u0027m going to change this to a AutomationControllerImpl internal class instead of using this trick.\n\nI\u0027d like to keep this declared in the get() method, though, otherwise I\u0027d have to have the LazyInstance declared after the AutomationControllerImpl at file scope, which is less readable than having it in the method.\n\nclass AutomationControllerImpl { ... };\nstatic LazyInstance\u003cAutomationControllerImpl\u003e sInstance;",
      "parentUuid": "b32f1dc5_0297ee6d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 29,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "003522c62b25c2dacfaeb0e982edd4f304d2c9bd",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
